With the HST you could see a firefly in Australia from Washington. With a 28-power telescope you can see it on the moon 250000 miles away. The telescope is 42.  Lennard Fisk, NASA's chief scientist, predicts that the Hubble telescope will literally be the dawn of a new era in astronomy.  Chaisson, a senior scientist at the Space Telescope Science Institute in Baltimore. In the history of optical astronomy there have been two great leaps in the resolution of the universe: Galileo's telescope in the autumn of 1609, and the Hubble Space Telescope in April 1990. 